name: $resourceType
desc: Returns the FHIR type name for this instance

name: $masterIdentifier
desc: Returns: Document identifier as assigned by the source of the document. This identifier is specific to this version of the document. This unique identifier may be used elsewhere to identify this version of the document.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: Document identifier as assigned by the source of the document. This identifier is specific to this version of the document. This unique identifier may be used elsewhere to identify this version of the document.

name: $identifier
desc: Returns: Other identifiers associated with the document, including version independent identifiers.

name: $addidentifier
desc: Other identifiers associated with the document, including version independent identifiers.

lvardefs.name: objRef
lvardefs.desc: Other identifiers associated with the document, including version independent identifiers.

name: $status
desc: Returns: The status of this document reference.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: The status of this document reference.

name: $docStatus
desc: Returns: The status of the underlying document.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: The status of the underlying document.

name: $::type
desc: Returns: Specifies the particular kind of document referenced  (e.g. History and Physical, Discharge Summary, Progress Note). This usually equates to the purpose of making the document referenced.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: Specifies the particular kind of document referenced  (e.g. History and Physical, Discharge Summary, Progress Note). This usually equates to the purpose of making the document referenced.

name: $class
desc: Returns: A categorization for the type of document referenced - helps for indexing and searching. This may be implied by or derived from the code specified in the DocumentReference.type.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: A categorization for the type of document referenced - helps for indexing and searching. This may be implied by or derived from the code specified in the DocumentReference.type.

name: $subject
desc: Returns: Who or what the document is about. The document can be about a person, (patient or healthcare practitioner), a device (e.g. a machine) or even a group of subjects (such as a document about a herd of farm animals, or a set of patients that share a common exposure).

name: $created
desc: Returns: When the document was created.

name: $indexed
desc: Returns: When the document reference was created.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: When the document reference was created.

name: $author
desc: Returns: Identifies who is responsible for adding the information to the document.

name: $addauthor
desc: Identifies who is responsible for adding the information to the document.

lvardefs.name: objRef
lvardefs.desc: Identifies who is responsible for adding the information to the document.

name: $authenticator
desc: Returns: Which person or organization authenticates that this document is valid.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: Which person or organization authenticates that this document is valid.

name: $custodian
desc: Returns: Identifies the organization or group who is responsible for ongoing maintenance of and access to the document.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: Identifies the organization or group who is responsible for ongoing maintenance of and access to the document.

name: $relatesTo
desc: Returns: Relationships that this document has with other document references that already exist.

name: $addrelatesTo
desc: Relationships that this document has with other document references that already exist.

lvardefs.name: objRef
lvardefs.desc: Relationships that this document has with other document references that already exist.

name: $description
desc: Returns: Human-readable description of the source document. This is sometimes known as the "title".

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: Human-readable description of the source document. This is sometimes known as the "title".

name: $securityLabel
desc: Returns: A set of Security-Tag codes specifying the level of privacy/security of the Document. Note that DocumentReference.meta.security contains the security labels of the "reference" to the document, while DocumentReference.securityLabel contains a snapshot of the security labels on the document the reference refers to.

name: $addsecurityLabel
desc: A set of Security-Tag codes specifying the level of privacy/security of the Document. Note that DocumentReference.meta.security contains the security labels of the "reference" to the document, while DocumentReference.securityLabel contains a snapshot of the security labels on the document the reference refers to.

name: $content
desc: Returns: The document and format referenced. There may be multiple content element repetitions, each with a different format.

name: $addcontent
desc: The document and format referenced. There may be multiple content element repetitions, each with a different format.

lvardefs.name: objRef

name: $context
desc: Returns: The clinical context in which the document was prepared.
